  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Find the optimal constant $c>0$ such that the following holds. \n\nFor all sufficiently large $N$, if $A\\sqcup B=\\{1,\\ldots,2N\\}$ is a partition into two equal parts, so that $\\lvert A\\rvert=\\lvert B\\rvert=N$, then there is some $x$ such that the number of solutions to $a-b=x$ with $a\\in A$ and $b\\in B$ is at least $cN$.",
